comment.body:
@Muja: Still a database of torrents technically. :P

Ignoring my joke, some people really don't want to host certain kinds of content, especially if they don't want to waste space for whatever reason. A distributed torrent site should be able to accommodate something like that. And for those worrying about censorship, I'm pretty sure there will be plenty of people willing to seed the NSFW hubs :)

The other benefit to having the torrents in hubs is that it emphasizes the fact that anybody could create their own torrent site front-end and then tap into the same hubs. This also solves the issues that some sites like ZeroTorrent have had where a user would run out of their allowed space on the site preventing them from making more uploads. With a hub system the user could simply switch to a different hub and continue uploading without having to hope that the creator of whatever site will up the user space allotment.
